review_blob: A good ale with a fair amount of hop.  Good carbonation level.  Stronger flower accents and a slight apple note in the after-taste (green, maybe granny smith or unrippened red delicious).  Does have a sweet maltiness but finishes bitter.

Overall, not impressed.  First off there may have been some skunk to this, then again it may have been an intended flavor.  Very wet palate, with far less appeal than a Newcastle.  ok color and decent head, but I prefer my beer to accel in flovor overall, and this one did not for me....Also, the label was different...yellow with a woman an a swing.
Really good....Chocolate bar flavor, with a shot of espresso.  Thick and smooth mouthfeel, with a fair amount of carbonation.

Did somebody open a can of beets...that was the first thought that entered my head...It really smells like beets.  It has a gently sweet flavor, but with a good helping of hop and malt flavors.  Rich feel.  The flavor does linger between sips.
This is one of my favorite beers.  It is very drinkable.  Has a caramel nutty taste.  Good amount of carbonation to make this refreshing on a hot day when served ice cold.  Very smooth finish.

I pretty much dont even remember tasting this one...I had a couple of sips and sniffs just to see what it was like.  I thought it was a very plain tasting dubbel...It distinctly reminded me of something...I said it out loud, but I cant remember...I will update when it comes to me, or when one of the guys that was there helps me out.
Pretty good dopple.  Sweet and malty.  Not a big fan of dopples in general.  Smooth mouthfeel. Short head.  Malty and toffee, maybe caramel.  Smells like a box of raisins.

Great bourbon beer.  Fairly sweet oaky tast.  Smooth as silk.  Definately fired cask flavor.  Thick mouthfeel.  Thick coating on the glass, with a deep brown color.  Thin head with larger sized bubbles.

Good strong stout with pretty hard espresso and dark or bakers chocolate.  Bitter like this type of stout should be, but also fairly sweet.  Black in color with a large bubbled shallow head of light tan.  Pretty good.

This is one of my new favorites.  A very good malty taste with a hint of sweetness like caramel or those roasted sugar coated nuts that they sell at county fairs.  Great brown gold with a nice tan head.  Not too think, but not so thin that it washes away like water.
An excelent drink.
Far better than miller...not really a high quality beer.  meant for drinking, and drinking lots...lots of carbonation.  quenches ones thinst - gets one drunk.
rich, creamy, sweet, and mellow.  has a carmel flavor with good feel...good carbonation level and great aroma...great sweet after dinner beer.
A good beer...far superior to heineken.  I still think that all beers in this class have a somewhat skunky smell.  this one has a very smooth taste and is very refreshing.
Great vibrant color...almost pumpkin pie color.  Light maltiness and pretty strong hop.  Pretty drinkable...3 pints anyway.
Dark roast here.  High in bitter hop bite.  Notes of chocolate, and coffee.  Maybe a tiny bit too carbonated.  Not a typical porter in myu opinion, this almost reminds me of a hopped up stout.
Sweet roasted malt aroma with slight hop hints.  Great taste, nice and dry finish.  Slight bite from the carbonation.  Seems to be like a porter-stout mix.  I am missing the spice.
beer_name: Big Sky Moose Drool Brown Ale

review_blob: Slightly nutty, malty aroma. Smooth, but watery mouthfeel.  Just about right on the carbonation.  Sweet caramel note.  Fairly bitter hop aftertaste.  Not nearly as good as a New Castle Brown Ale due to the watered-down aspect.

Deep yellow color - too much like urine.  Somewhat like a heavy miller or pabst.  Not much maltiness or hops.  Slight soapy metalic nip on the sides of your tongue.  Serve very cold so as to prevent getting too much of the taste and its not bad.
beer_name: Flying Dog Tire Bite Golden Ale

review_blob: Decent, but not really outstanding.  Some upfront bitter hopiness, faded fast into wateriness.  I found it a little too light on the malt.  Surprisingly filling for a red.  Also found the flavor to degrade with rising temperature.  I also found the flavor to be soapy like brownaler.
beer_name: Flying Dog Old Scratch Amber Lager

review_blob:
I rated this one before, but it must not have posted....It was very poetic - fitting for such a beer.
There are so many deScriptions of this beer that i probably could not say anything that has not been said.
Dark chocolately, roasted, think, sweet, lingering, powerfull, smooth, and mind-numbing.
beer_name: Three Floyds Dark Lord Russian Imperial Stout

review_blob: Disappointing.  Very thin for a stout.  Not much to the flavor other than over roasted barley.  I honestly just had this last night in the micro beer tent at the WI state fair...I actually pour almost all of it down the drain.  It just plain was not a good stout.  When everybody says a lactic sweetness, I think htey really mean acidic bitterness.  No richness in this stout.
Pretty good - not great.  Much lick Leinnes Big Butt Dopple Bock.  Malty smell and taste - lightly sweet - slightly bitter.  I think that this is the official beer of Texas Road House Restaurants.

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: More like a mix of winecooler and honeyweis than a real beer.  Good none the less.  Berry and wheat.  Pretty color looks good in a pretty girls hand during summer:-)

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: Deep yellow slightly orange hue.  Mild ale, slightly sweet, but not so much from honey.  Highly carbonated with atall head of somewhat larger, short lived bubbles...Almost chanpagne like.  Good served ice cold.

I dont really know what urine tastes like, but I have to beleive that this beer is not too far off the mark for replicating that flavor.  This crap is so bad that you almost have to pinch your nose as you drink it.  I now know why college kids slug these down so fast - its because they cant stand the taste either - beleive me, this is ***NOT*** Milwaukees best beer.

See rating for Bud Lite...CRAP with a capital C, R, A, P!!!  No hops, no malt, just pale yellow fizzy water with a little corn alcohol added to give the college kiddies, and bar slobs a little buzz and a lot of gas.
This is a decent, inexpensive lager.  Crisp taste, best served out of the freezer.  Quite a bit of fizz, but as long as it is cold this does not bother.
UPDATED: JUN 22, 2005
No head, fizzy like soda.  Looks like a darker old english.  Tastes much different.  Sweet, slightly thick.  Not too shabby.

Almost zero head...Motor oil color.  Rich and creamy mouth feel, interrupted by a slight nip of carbonation, coating the tongue with roasted malt aftertaste.  Starts sweet on the tongue but rapidly contorts to a strong bitter malty flavor.  Definate chocolate and coffee presence.  This beer has a very heavy feel to it.  Very good!

Pretty good stout.  Very dark, with a stong creamy light brown head.  I cant really comment on the smell due to a terrible cold...also my taste senses are slightly dulled, but that didnt keep me from enjoying this one.  The was a strong bitter bite that lingered only a few seconds to finish quite dry.  Roasted malt and chocolate hit me most.  Just thick enough for stout.  Best thing is that it is named for one of the best card games that more than 99.9% of the world just doesnt get, and of the select that do, 99.9% of are terrible at it.  Learn/master the game, then try the beer again...youll have a new appreciation for it.

This was one of the most spectacular appearance beers that I have ever had...This could be due to the fact that it was served in one of those vintage schlitz glasses with the light in the bottom(RAMERBOY01, again)  The color was a beautiful volcanic sunset orange.  Taste was good, the smoked chipotle was very evident.  Light maltiness, little to no hop.  There was pretty much no "hot bite" in my opinion, though, I drink habanero smoothies and p*ss tobasco, so it might really be there and I am just not getting it.
Very good in every sense...I dont have anything bad to say about it, execpt that I dont have any more of it.  Easy to drink....very quenching....mild, and no skunky flavor.   Good stuff.
beer_name: JosephsBrau Black Toad Distinctive Dark Ale

review_blob:
Wow, thats good!  Nice sweet molassis aroma.  Great colored head, like brown sugar, though not a whole lot of it:-(   Very smooth the whole way down.  Reminds me of having a good candy bar after not having one for a long time.  As thick at whole milk, and as dark as a 9 month overdue oil change on an 83 Delta88.  Pretty filling though.  Maybe a tiny bit on the sweet side, but with a salty snack thats a good thing.

Thanks to my good friend and beer ambasador, rayboy01, for this one.  Cheers to you.

HOP!  In a word, HOP.  Did I mention the hoppy hopiness.  By the way, there is a lot of hop to this hop hop hop hop hopyhop.   Lastly, youll notice the undertones of hop in this glass of liquified hops.

Great attempt at replicating MGD light.  Not sure I see the point in this, but great attempt anyway.
Decent macro - clean - washes down whatever slop you are eating, but then so does water.
Certainly would not drink for the flavor, or any other characteristics.  Pretty much one of those beers that is just drunk because it is there and so are you, and you want to either get a buzz and/or hold something cold in you hand for a while so you dont have to put your hands in your pockets and look like a putz.

Truly the best tasting Huber beer.  Now, thats not saying much, but give it a try, and you may find that if you are at a back yard bbq, and all there is to drink is cheap macrobrewpee and this - your decision will be simple - drink out of the toilet!
Seriously though, this beer is Not Terrible, definately drinkable, but Not Even Close To Great.  Little sweet, somewhat coffe-like, and only to be consumed frigidly cold - see note.
***Important Note - Never let you Huber Bock reach critical temperature, or you will not be able to avoid the gag reflex.

Ill drink it if my faucet is broken.

Consequently, my good buddy Lucas Finco used to think that this beer is the greatest beer on earth.  He would buy a case for about 6 dollars.
